<br>
<br>
After some duels on Pendragon I have found it is much harder to keep someone interupted via shouts. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=staraswift>StaraSwift</A> at: 1/28/04 7:02 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=narg@teamskald>Narg</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/28/04 8:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=803.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Incoming Indirect Skald Nerf number 23534258123</span><hr size=1> Well, that should get folks of the &quot;skalds are ment to be the ultimate interrupters&quot; kick.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=staraswift>StaraSwift</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/28/04 9:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=803.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Incoming Indirect Skald Nerf number 23534258123</span><hr size=1> So what do we get for having our role destroyed? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=herjulf>herjulf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/29/04 4:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=803.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hem.passagen.se/robemell/Herjulf.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Incoming Indirect Skald Nerf number 23534258123</span><hr size=1> Dont be so partial please.<br>
<br>
Consider the current state for casters.<br>
<br>
Everything interupts, DD, snare, mex, disease, aggro spells, a snease and a breeeze of fresh air.<br>
<br>
Personally my main is my skald i also have SM and a Shaman.<br>
Without MOC RA either of the two i mentioned can really perform vs anything in the game, all classes more or less have something to interrupt with.<br>
<br>
I very much would like to see interupts getting balanced a little more to give midgard a reason to get casters in grps again.<br>
<br>
As you may have noticed the in midgardians mind only &quot;valid&quot; grp setup atm is the steamroll grp with healers, warriors and savager/zerkas.<br>
<br>
Any change to interupts will help casters get back into the game.<br>
<br>
And i also am quite happy if it does i hate kiting casters/healer chars with my skald dd, snare, mezz to interupt them. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=courtjester@teamskald>CourtJester</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 72<br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/29/04 8:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=803.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> NERF!</span><hr size=1> I tend to agree with Herjulf on the interrupt part. However, casters, at least in Albion, have another problem, which overpowers them:<br>
<br>
I find myself in various 8v8 fights in which I get nuked FROM THE SAME CASTER for 500-800 damage, sometimes 1050 after debuff, at a rate of around 1 second. When I'm fully buffed, forgot to mention, although in such cases it doesn't make THAT much of a difference.<br>
<br>
With RA's and ToA bonuses, casters seem to pass the casting speed caps, so just think about such a caster group assisting each other.<br>
<br>
Devastating. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=amstellight>Amstel Light</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Fervent</span><br>  Posts: 131<br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/29/04 8:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=803.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: NERF!</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I very much would like to see interupts getting balanced a little more to give midgard a reason to get casters in grps again.<br>
<br>
As you may have noticed the in midgardians mind only &quot;valid&quot; grp setup atm is the steamroll grp with healers, warriors and savager/zerkas.<br>
<br>
Any change to interupts will help casters get back into the game.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<br>
Don't make this change more than it is.  Interupts have NEVER been a reason not to group casters.  The only reason casters are not getting groups right now is Determination.   Midgard can put together a mean 8 man grank group based around determination and casters just don't fit into that equation....except maybe a supp specced SM who is could at pealing off the healers/shaman.<br>
<br>
 <p>Sideshow lvl50 ML6 Skald</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rystian>Rystian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/29/04 9:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=803.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: NERF!</span><hr size=1> Your server is still running mostly Det Tank groups?  WOW!  They have mostly gone the way of the dodo lately on Guin (like 2 I know of still operate).  <br>
<br>
It's all about PBAE bombs.  Det Tanks cannot compete with the new casting speeds.  Most Det Tank groups now get destroyed before closing in.  <br>
<br>
This nerf does hurt the skald who travels with PBAE groups.  Of course, I'll just adapt my tactics.  Maybe now I have a reason to get Belt of the sun (faster hits on casters = more interrupting) and carry a shield.<br>
