</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=staraswift>StaraSwift</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/30/04 1:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=803.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: NERF!</span><hr size=1> Um /assist and spam styles?<br>
<br>
Whats done is not done.  Its called a Test Server.  Theres not really much to adapt with.  Our class is based around the use of 4 shouts.  Snare and Mez will always be essentially useless due to immunity timers.  They were good for interupting, but now they won't be.  I don't think theres anything else on the skald repertoire to come up with a new strategy based around.  Castable spells? Nope.  Guard/Slam?  Nope.  No, no other kind of utility, sorry.<br>
<br>
I liked being able to contribute to a fight with my shouts despite them doing little damage against buffed opponents.  Maybe its time now that they remove the DD shouts and give us 2.0 spec and shield.<br>
<br>
Personally I don't care about the current state for casters.  They're casting for 600 damage at sub 1 second speeds now.  PBAE groups dominate any server with a decent population. <br>
<br>
Interupter has been a role(other than autofollow speedbot) that has defined the Skald class primarily (and other offensive hybrids) for its lifecycle as a class, and will now disappear in the blink of an eye. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=staraswift>StaraSwift</A> at: 1/30/04 1:36 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hagarrd>Hagarrd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/30/04 3:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=803.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: NERF!</span><hr size=1> Erm,<br>
<br>
First off, which of you would turn this caster away from your group?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.camelotherald.com/chardisplay.php?s=Bedevere&c=12611">www.camelotherald.com/cha...re&c=12611</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
&quot;yeah, you... the first ever rr10 SM, I dont want you in my group... hit the road!&quot;<br>
<br>
Ive seen mid groups will 2 RMs and 2 SMs and a healer, a warrior, a skald, and a shaman just kick the living shit out of the uberl33t alb groups on Bedevere. Run that assist train right into nukes and 2 pbae superfast MoC SM's. Redcaps dont die that fast.<br>
<br>
This all falls back to &quot;90% of all problems with any class are player related/generated&quot;<br>
<br>
Dont QQ about how its going to be harder to interupt, just change your tactics to compensate.<br>
<br>
Sligg needs to spit some wisdom on this thread. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rystian>Rystian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/30/04 8:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=803.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: NERF!</span><hr size=1> We actually usually run 3 SMs, 2 healers, skald, cave shaman and one other (usually another skald actually) and are doing quite well.  This seems to be the growing formula for Guin PBAE Bombs.<br>
<br>
Now, Can I still interrupt?  Yes.  Is it going to be harder?  Yes.  Do I provide any other utility?  Well, YES.  You never actually see the damage add in my group for instance (no need), so when the fight really kicks in, we get 2 20% resists going (primary damage types) to compensate for no Aug healer (unless we have an Aug healer, which is rare).  <br>
<br>
Skalds have more than just 4 instas.  I don't care how long you have been playing Stara, if you break us down to just Speed, weapon and 4 shouts, you have not really explored the class.  We have a lot of situational tools.  As long as you use them, there is always something you can pull out.<br>
<br>
How will I compensate?  Faster weapons (to move around more).  I'll do less damage, but I'm not the primary damage dealer in my group.  More charged items.  Expensive, but can save a group if needed.  Switching targets on the fly (Melee still interrupts for a few seconds).  Basically, I'll work around whatever they threw at us.  I'll keep providing the speed that my group needs.  I'll provide resists.  Sometimes, even the heal chant is useful after a big fight.<br>
<br>
<br>
BTW, we destroy assist trains.  They don't stand a chance.<br>
