<br>
I've run and continue to run in both pbae and melee groups.  PBAE groups may be an excellent source of vitamins R and P but I've never actually had to DO anything in the group other than just play speed, anything else I happened to throw in was just gravy.  The SMs do all the work and then some.  Melee groups on the other hand I'm forced to fight tooth and nail to melee one casting/healing class while using my shouts to interupt a second and everything that I added to the group with interupts and melee was valuable.  I like getting 8 pages of /rudes in the middle of a fight from the druid that I'm not allowing to get off one single spell. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=staraswift>StaraSwift</A> at: 1/30/04 11:46 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=etherag>Etherag</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/30/04 11:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=803.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: NERF!</span><hr size=1> Rystian,<br>
<br>
Don’t bank everything on the PBAoE groups.  Like all tactics they have some weakness.  Yes they are fun and yes they CAN be effective but if you go against good Hib or Alb groups both can easy take it down.  <br>
<br>
We ran this way a good part of the summer and after about 6 weeks the hibs and albs both figured ways to get around it.  For hibs all they need is group purge.  We mez, they purge, SMs are getting in position and Splat, you have a big group of pissed Hibs sitting on your casters.  We ran into this all the time and it’s even worse when you meet up with a group that has 2 GP.  This does not even take into account self purge or Det.  Our healers go so tired of being purged every time they threw CC they both respected to Aug.<br>
<br>
Albs can be even worse if they know what they are doing.  Fortunately most don’t but the combination of bolt range mez, SoS or BoF can all throw the SM Bomb squad into a tail spin.  <br>
<br>
Det Tank groups are not perfect either but just as they are not as effective killing machines they also are not as easy to take apart.<br>
<br>
Just my 2 cents.<br>
<br>
Oh and after being nuked the other day by a Alb caster for 450 5 times in about 10 seconds (RR6 Cabalist to my RR5 Skald, no idea on spec) with my full resists, I don’t have a lot of sympathy for the poor plight of casters.   ToA gear with its +casting speed, + debuff and + spell damage can make for some very overpowering people.  To be honest she killed me so fast i did not even have time to turn, locate her and close.  Only got within 1000 range.<br>
